				<h4 style="color:white">How to make a website in Github?</h4>
				<p style="color: white">Step 1. Create a Github account or log into your existing Github account</p>
				<p style="color: white">Step 2. Create a new repository by clicking on the "Create repository" button on the left or click the "+" on the near top-right corner then "New repository"</p>
				<p style="color: white">Step 3. IMPORTANT! In the repository name, you have to name that repository {your_username}.github.io (Replace the {your_username} with your username, example: example.github.io), make sure that the repo is public then press "Create repository"</p>
				<p style="color: white">Step 4. After that, create a new file and name that file "index.html" (without quotes). This will be the file that load into the browser when type the address in</p>
				<p style="color: white">Step 5. Add your HTML code into the file, type the address into the address bar and the website should show up</p>
